GetProperty(Type, String)

Walks up the inheritance heirarchy looking for a property with the name specified at each level This is neccessary because, when the "override" or "new" keyword is on a property accessor, several properties have the same name. In these cases, the Type.GetProperty(string name) method throws and "Ambiguous..." exception Walking from the most derived type up the heirachy guarantees that the most overridden if found first.

IsPropertyMappedToThis(PropertyInfo)

Sometimes a single property in one model maps to the whole object of the other model. This occurs primarily when an inheritance in one model maps to an aggregation in the other. When this occurs, a [Map("this")] should be placed on the property
